cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.IR 

The paper proposes a framework for object detection and segmentation in medical images, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The use of intermediate abstract representations and the development of a new loss function suggest a focus on machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI). The application of the framework to retinal images suggests a potential fit for multimedia (cs.MM) and information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-categories.
